No need to install or compile anything.
The package contains just bash and python scripts,
Apertium, GF, a bash shell and a python interpreter (2.6+) are required.

The following additional packages are required for learning multi-word expressions from parallel corpora:
- GF python bindings
- moreutils (http://joeyh.name/code/moreutils/), which provides the command-line tool "parallel"
- Python PuLP (http://pythonhosted.org/PuLP/main/installing_pulp_at_home.html)
- The Moses statistical machine translation toolkit (http://www.statmt.org/moses/)